UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0304393202001770
KW  - Reserve requirements
KW  - Business fluctuations
AB  - When trade is uncertain and sequential, a fractional reserve banking system may give rise to endogenous monetary shocks. These endogenous monetary shocks lead to fluctuations in capacity utilization and waste. When fluctuations in the currency/deposit ratio are the important source of the monetary shocks, a high reserve requirement on checkable accounts can minimize this waste. When fluctuations in the fraction of credit-card transactions are important, then low reserve requirements will minimize waste.
